  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Risk by Probability Cost is used to determine the impact risks could have on the project.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For each identified&amp;nbsp;risk, calculate its probability cost.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Probability Cost = probability of a risk occurring&amp;nbsp;x&amp;nbsp;its consequence cost&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Establish probability&amp;nbsp;cost ranges and count the number of risks in each range.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A good way to monitor Risk by Probability Cost is to use a bar chart. Plot number of risks on the Y axis and&#xD;
    probability cost ranges on the X axis.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A&amp;nbsp;large number&amp;nbsp;of risks in the high probability cost ranges is cause for concern. The team should determine&#xD;
    what actions are needed to mitigate these risks (e.g. addressing any uncertainties in the project due to new&#xD;
    technologies, or use cases requiring clarification with stakeholders).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    As the project progresses and this metric is monitored over time, the number of risks in the high probability cost&#xD;
    ranges should decrease, indicating that the team is addressing high impact risks as early as possible in the lifecycle.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Below is an example of a Risk by Probability Cost report for the Online Auction project in Smarter Planet program.&#xD;
    X-axis is the measured in probability cost and Y-axis is the number of risks.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;Risk by Probability Cost chart&quot; src=&quot;resources/risk_by_probability_cost.gif&quot; width=&quot;532&quot; height=&quot;533&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>The team reviews Risk by Probability Cost at the end of each iteration during their end of iteration assessment.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Project Conductor&amp;reg; and IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Team Concert&amp;reg;&amp;nbsp;collect risk data.&amp;nbsp; IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg;&#xD;
    Insight&amp;reg;&amp;nbsp;provides an out of the box report for this metric.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
